ABAKALIKI – The Indigenous People of Biafra (IPOB) has announced a bounty of one million naira for anybody who provide the group with any credible information on the subsequent overseas trips of any of the South East governors as well as other corrupt leaders from the zone. The leader of the group, Mazi Nnamdi Kanu made the announcement on Sunday evening during a live broadcast on the heels of the attack on the former Deputy President of the Senate, Ike Ekweremadu in Nuremberg, Germany on Saturday. Powered by RubiQube Ad Network Mr. Kanu said that the group has stationed its members in over 100 countries across the World to hound, harass and attack South East governors and other leaders from the Zone who refuse to speak up against the injustice being meted to the zone by the Federal Government. He disclosed that they attacked Chief Ekweremadu in Germany because he had never made any serious effort to speak and at and for the zone before the Federal Government despite his important position in Nigeria government. In the broadcast, Mr. Kanu also berated the President of Ohanaeze Ndigbo, Nnia Nwodo, for allegedly working with Nigerian government to launch Operation Python Dance in the zone which he said claimed lives of many of its members and other innocent Biafrans.